#: ../../../tutorials/dto-tutorial/02-nested-exclude.rst:2
msgid "Excluding from nested models"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/dto-tutorial/02-nested-exclude.rst:4
msgid ""
"The ``exclude`` option can be used to exclude fields from models that are "
"related to our data model by using dotted paths. For example, ``exclude={\"a."
"b\"}`` would exclude the ``b`` attribute of an instance nested on the ``a`` "
"attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/dto-tutorial/02-nested-exclude.rst:7
msgid ""
"To demonstrate, let's adjust our script to add an ``Address`` model, that is "
"related to the ``Person`` model:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/dto-tutorial/02-nested-exclude.rst:10
msgid ""
"from __future__ import annotations\n"
"\n"
"from dataclasses import dataclass\n"
"\n"
"from litestar import Litestar, get\n"
"from litestar.dto import DataclassDTO, DTOConfig\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@dataclass\n"
"class Address:\n"
"    street: str\n"
"    city: str\n"
"    country: str\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@dataclass\n"
"class Person:\n"
"    name: str\n"
"    age: int\n"
"    email: str\n"
"    address: Address\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class ReadDTO(DataclassDTO[Person]):\n"
"    config = DTOConfig(exclude={\"email\", \"address.street\"})\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@get(\"/person/{name:str}\", return_dto=ReadDTO, sync_to_thread=False)\n"
"def get_person(name: str) -> Person:\n"
"    # Your logic to retrieve the person goes here\n"
"    # For demonstration purposes, a placeholder Person instance is returned\n"
"    address = Address(street=\"123 Main St\", city=\"Cityville\", "
"country=\"Countryland\")\n"
"    return Person(name=name, age=30, email=f\"email_of_{name}@example.com\", "
"address=address)\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"app = Litestar(route_handlers=[get_person])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/dto-tutorial/02-nested-exclude.rst:14
msgid ""
"The ``Address`` model has three attributes, ``street``, ``city``, and "
"``country``, and we've added an ``address`` attribute to the ``Person`` "
"model."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/dto-tutorial/02-nested-exclude.rst:17
msgid ""
"The ``ReadDTO`` class has been updated to exclude the ``street`` attribute "
"of the nested ``Address`` model using the dotted path syntax ``\"address."
"street\"``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/dto-tutorial/02-nested-exclude.rst:20
msgid ""
"Inside the handler, we create an ``Address`` instance and assign it to the "
"``address`` attribute of the ``Person``."
msgstr ""

